â™ª

39:31.369 --> 39:33.545
â™ª

39:45.687 --> 39:49.430
We're back at the scene
of the crime. Why?

39:49.474 --> 39:51.519
Can you get the trunk
for me?

39:51.563 --> 39:54.043
Anybody order some
new plexiglass?

39:54.087 --> 39:56.742
Officer Reagan.What are you doing?

39:56.785 --> 39:58.483
I came to, uh,
replace the plexiglass

39:58.526 --> 39:59.484
here on your counter.

39:59.527 --> 40:01.486
I don't understand.

40:01.529 --> 40:02.748
Also gonna have some
uniformed officers come by

40:02.791 --> 40:05.359
and check on your store
a few times a day.

40:05.403 --> 40:06.882
Thank you.

40:06.926 --> 40:08.362
Good.

40:08.406 --> 40:11.104
All right, well, you got
Phillips-head that'll fit these?

40:16.022 --> 40:17.371
Hmm.

40:17.415 --> 40:21.419
Three words that I would say
to my 18-year-old self.

40:21.462 --> 40:22.550
Mm-hmm.

40:22.594 --> 40:26.032
Marry Jamie Reagan.

40:31.820 --> 40:33.039
Hey.

40:33.082 --> 40:36.477
That's a pretty girly drink.Well, I can be

40:36.521 --> 40:38.044
girly sometimes.

40:38.087 --> 40:39.437
I got you a beer.

40:39.480 --> 40:41.613
Perfect. You read my mind.

40:43.005 --> 40:46.356
I am regretting
opening this case.

40:46.400 --> 40:48.576
I didn't know
how complicated it would get.

40:48.620 --> 40:50.491
Well, it gets
even more complicated.

40:50.535 --> 40:52.667
Turns out Reggie Lewis
also has kids.

40:52.711 --> 40:56.018
In fact, one of 'em's
a congresswoman in Brooklyn.

40:56.062 --> 40:57.585
Shannon Lewis?

40:57.629 --> 41:00.893
She heard about the arrest.
She's planned a press conference

41:00.936 --> 41:03.069
on the steps of Borough Hall
tomorrow.

41:03.112 --> 41:04.723
Great.

41:04.766 --> 41:06.725
You got any other good news?

41:06.768 --> 41:08.553
If it makes you feel any better,

41:08.596 --> 41:10.816
I admire you for what you do.

41:12.165 --> 41:14.733
For sticking my nose
where it doesn't belong

41:14.776 --> 41:16.822
and embarrassing my boss.

41:16.865 --> 41:18.301
Look, Sandra Harris
killed a guy,

41:18.345 --> 41:20.608
and a life is a life
no matter how complicated

41:20.652 --> 41:22.480
it makes things for Crawford.

41:22.523 --> 41:24.699
She probably hates me now.

41:24.743 --> 41:27.485
Nah.
She hated you way before this.

41:27.528 --> 41:30.009
Thanks.

41:33.186 --> 41:34.361
[vocalizing]

41:34.404 --> 41:36.450
Let's give it up
for Sheryl!

41:36.494 --> 41:38.626
[cheering]

41:40.367 --> 41:41.499
That was good.

41:41.542 --> 41:43.152
Fun, right?

41:43.196 --> 41:44.632
You ever get up there
and grab the mic?

41:44.676 --> 41:45.851
Course I do.Mm.

41:45.894 --> 41:48.331
What's your karaoke
go-to song?

41:48.375 --> 41:49.985
"I Will Survive."

41:50.029 --> 41:51.900
Mm, Gloria Gaynor.

41:51.944 --> 41:55.251
That's a kick-ass song.Thank you. Uh...

41:55.295 --> 41:56.862
I see what you're doing there.

41:56.905 --> 41:58.864
I'm not doing anything,
that's really my favorite song.

41:58.907 --> 42:02.215
Okay, who's next up?

42:05.610 --> 42:08.134
Me!

42:08.177 --> 42:10.223
I'm next.

42:11.398 --> 42:12.617
What are you doing?

42:12.660 --> 42:16.403
You said I should
start having some fun.

42:16.446 --> 42:18.361
Let's have some fun.

42:18.405 --> 42:20.842
[laughs]Gimme that mic!

